  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Photograph</ab>
      <ab type="lido:event" subtype="creation">
        <date>1939</date>
      <persName role="Photographer"><forename>Alija M.</forename><surname>Akšamija</surname><ref type="context" target="info:fedora/context:siba.pn.be7b6d09">Akšamija, Alija M.</ref></persName></ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Roma man against a spectacular view of Sarajevo from the east. He is posing on the right margin of the landscape photograph, presenting the city with a large smile. He is dressed in a padded jacket, over it a <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=J1">jelek</ref>, an <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=A2">ahmedija</ref> on his head and a belt with a leather <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=B18">bensilah</ref> around his waist. In his right hand he is holding a bottle, his left rests on his hip. The shot of Sarajevo unfolding to his right is carefully geometrically arranged: The <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=K5">kafana</ref> on <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=B1">Babića bašča</ref>, Šabanova Kafana in <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=B7">Bentbaša</ref> and the <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=V2">Vijećnica</ref> form a triangle. The bridge in <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=B7">Bentbaša</ref> and the path leading up to <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=B1">Babića bašča</ref> are at the same angle and meet exactly in the centre of the lower frame. Next to the <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=V2">Vijećnica</ref>, the regulated part of the Miljacka is visible almost at a right angle to the <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=B7">Bentbaša</ref> section in the foreground.</ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet" subtype="comment">The photograph was probably taken on the way up to <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=Z7">Žuta tabija</ref>. Analogue photographic process, negative-positive (Agfa Isopan 17 DIN). Original preserved as a positive on silver bromine paper, stored as a print and a digital record.</ab>
